<h1>&gt; &gt; spoilers</h1>

<h2>Episode 3.01- The Aftermath</h2>

<p>When The O.C. returns for its third season premiere, Ryan, Marissa, Seth and Summer are about to begin their senior year at Harbor High. But while everyone else celebrates the last days of summer, a dark cloud hangs over the foursome. Trey, Ryan's brother, still clings to life two months after the shooting and the cops want to know who really shot him. Will Ryan take the fall for Marissa? Meanwhile, Julie Cooper and Marissa's father, Jimmy, are determined to protect Marissa at whatever cost. And while Sandy, Seth and Ryan try to fend for themselves at home, Kirsten, still recovering in her plush rehab by the sea, forms a friendship with fellow recovering alcoholic Charlotte (Jeri Ryan), who – like all things in the O.C. – may not be everything she appears to be. Source: <a href="http://teentvmovies.about.com/od/theocspoilers/a/theocs3prem.htm">About.com</a></p>

<p>The summer is soon over and school is starting in a few days. Trey has been in a coma since Marissa shot him. The D.A. has waited as long as possible for Trey to wake up but people are starting to demand answers and justice, which is why D.D.A. Chris Caldwell was asked to dig around and take more depositions from Ryan, Seth and Marissa amongst others. Will either Marissa or Ryan pay the price? Or will both be prosecuted? Kirsten is still at the rehab center. Julie is mad because Caleb's accountant says it will take months before the will can be read. Summer, Sandy and Jimmy also appear. Source: <a href="http://www.spoilerfix.com">Spoilerfix</a></p>

<h2>Episode 3.02- The Shape of Things to Come</h2>

<p>Jimmy meets a man named Don at the Yatch Club's bar. He and Don talk about Jimmy's money problems. Julie and Sandy have a meeting with the Dean and Dr. Kim. Later, Ryan and Marissa have a meeting with the Dean to talk about their future (or lack of) at Harbor. Sandy drives to the house of Charlotte, one of the ladies who was in rehab with Kirsten. There he meets Kirsten, who seems to have decided to live there for a while. Summer and Marissa are in the student lounge at school where a fellow student, Taylor, talks about her project for the school's carnival… thing is it'’s Marissa's meeting not Taylor's. Taylor has been fighting over Social Chair with Marissa since they were freshmen. Will Marissa remain as Social Chair? Source <a href="http://www.spoilerfix.com">Spoilerfix</a></p>

<h2>Episode 3.03- The End Of...</h2>

<p>Jimmy must make once more the difficult decision to leave or stay with his family. Charlotte has to leave her house. Marissa, Ryan, and Sandy also appear in the episode. Source <a href="http://www.spoilerfix.com">Spoilerfix</a></p>

<h2>Episode 3.04</h2>

<p>Marissa goes to Newport Union, a public school. At the end of the day, she meets Johnny Harper, a 17-year-old student who seems to like the beach and to skateboard. His girlfriend Casey and their friend Dennis "Chili" Childress joins them. Chili invites Marissa on a date but she says she already has a boyfriend. The next day, it's "Newport Union Back to School Dance," Marissa is unsure she should go. The news about the Trey schooting makes its way to Newport Union which crushes Marissa as she was hoping to get a fresh start. Johnny tries to cheer her up. Ryan, Seth and Summer appear in the episode. Source <a href="http://www.spoilerfix.com">Spoilerfix</a></p>

<h2>General Season Three Spoilers</h2>

<p>Eric Mabius will play the Dean of Discipline at Harbor, and Jeri Ryan will guest star in seven episodes as Charlotte Morgan, whom Kirsten meets in rehab. Source: <a href="http://thehollywoodreporter.com/thr/index.jsp">The Hollywood Reporter</a></p>

<p>While it appears that Jimmy will make a return to Newport, Josh won't say whether or not he will be coming back for sure. Source: <a href="http://tv.zap2it.com/tveditorial/tve_main/1,1002,276|96693|1|,00.html">Zap2it</a></p>

<p>Josh has also said that &quot;Somebody will be leaving the show that you might not expect and somebody will be coming back.&quot; Source: <a href="http://tv.zap2it.com/tveditorial/tve_main/1,1002,276|96693|1|,00.html">Zap2it</a></p>

<p>If Amanda Righetti's now show &quot;Reunion&quot; goes the way of &quot;North Shore,&quot; she may be back to play Hailey on The O.C. Source: <a href='http://www.tvguide.com/news/askausiello/">Ask Ausiello</a></p>

<p>Navi Rawat (Theresa) expects to come back to wrap up her storyline when they need her. Source: <a href="http://www.eonline.com/Gossip/Kristin/">Kristen at E! Online</a></p>

<p>Regarding plans for next year, Schwartz says, &quot;Year three, for us, is going to be senior year, so obviously that's a huge event in these kids' lives, and for their parents as well. So we'll be dealing with all sorts of things, like what does the future hold, college, graduation, all those kind of gigantic, kind of epic events in high school life.&quot; Source <a href="http://www.tv.zap2it.com">Zap2it</a></p>

